CatDescriptText: Cutline of images published in the Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1955, pg. 12 reads: "Teen-Queen Contestants - These fourteen young misses of the Hill District are vying for the title Teen-Queen in the annual contest sponsored by Hill City.  They are, left to right:...Barbara Harris [and unknown woman]"
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Barbara Harris wearing light colored short sleeved sheer blouse with smocking, and hoop earrings, posed in front of light colored background for Hill City Teen Queen contestant; Portrait of unknown young woman wearing light colored short sleeved blouse with collar bar, dark neck scarf, and earrings, posed in front of light colored background for Hill City Teen Queen contest
